Do you remember these guitar riffs? Of course you do!

These five iconic guitar riffs were definitely at the forefront of the 90's sound. Being at the forefront also meant being the actual 
leaders driving the sound of a generation. Obviously, most of the bands glory days were in the 90's, even for am older band that came
out of the 70's. 

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fSxxLt9nOUI" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

1. Lenny Kravitz "Are You Gonna go My Way"
2. Sublime "What I Got"
3. Smashing Pumpkins "1979"
4. AC/DC "Thunderstruck"
5. Temple of the Dog "Hunger Strike
